data.title: Tetra Tech awarded £17 million water engineering design contract
data.description:
• Tetra Tech (TTEK) said on Thursday that it has been selected by Portsmouth Water for a £17 million water engineering design contract.
  • The company will provide engineering design and technical support to deliver resilient water service to its customers in Southern England and advance their programs to meet new regulatory targets.
  • Tetra Tech’s water engineers will design high-end solutions to improve critical infrastructure including reservoirs, pipes, and treatment plants that serve more than 700,000 people.
  • TTEK -0.47% premarket to $31.7.
  • Source: Press Release

data.title: ECB holds interest rate steady at 2%
data.description:
The European Central Bank kept its interest rates unchanged on Thursday for a third meeting in a row amid low inflation and steady growth.

The eurozone economy grew a better-than-expected 0.2% in the third quarter, flash data showed Thursday.

The ECB cut rates by a combined two percentage points in the year to June but has been on the sidelines since. The trim came as the eurozone's annual inflation rate hit 2%, the ECB’s target, though the rate of price rises has risen since, to 2.2% in September.

data.title: Fiserv downgraded at Morgan Stanley, Goldman Sachs to Hold-equivalent
data.description:
Fiserv (FI) was trading lower as Morgan Stanley and Goldman Sachs cut their recommendation on the stock to Hold-equivalent after the payment technology company's Q3 earnings release.

Shares were -3.23% Thursday pre-market to $68.32.

Yesterday, FI stock slumped 30% as the company revamped its leadership, refreshed its board, slashed its full-year earnings guidance, and launched a new action plan after its Q3 earnings fell short of Wall Street consensus.

"40 years of double-digit EPS growth ends. Downgrade to EW as mgmt goes through an investment process to improve service and product, targeting eventual mid-single-digit revenue growth and a return to double-digit EPS growth," said analyst James Faucette in a research note, downgrading the stock to Equal-weight from Overweight and slashing the price target to $81.00 from $179.00.

"The work will take time, and so will rebuilding investor confidence," added Faucette.

"While we had previewed a reset quarter in our earnings preview and were negative going into the quarter, the magnitude of the revisions surprised us, and the new mgmt highlighted numerous areas of the business where the prior focus was on short term strategies to drive revenue growth that were somewhat at odds with a client first mindset," said Goldman Sachs analysts Will Nance, Rajul Bothra, and Jack Evans.

"The bigger surprise was that the company would be reversing several aggressive pricing actions from recent years and lapping some one time revenue impacts that were not previously well understood," added the research note.

"Given these issues and the fact that the company is basically guiding to flat revenue for the next 9 months until the pricing reversals and one time revenue issues are lapped, we are downgrading shares from Buy to Neutral," said Goldman Sachs analysts with a price target of $79.00.

"We believe it will take time for investor sentiment to turn positive, which we think at a minimum will require the top line to reaccelerate and double digit EPS growth is back in reach," said the note.

The rating differs from the average sell-side analysts and Seeking Alpha authors rating of Buy. SA's Quant Rating system grades the stock as Sell.

Wearable Devices announces pricing of $3.3M direct offering
data.description:
• Wearable Devices (WLDS) said on Thursday that it has entered into a securities purchase agreement with an existing single institutional investor for the purchase and sale of 1.23M ordinary shares at a purchase price of $2.67 per share in a registered direct offering. 
  • The gross proceeds from the offering are expected to be approximately $3.3M. 
  • In addition, in a concurrent private placement, Wearable Devices will issue and sell unregistered warrants to purchase up to 1.23M ordinary shares. The warrants will have an exercise price of $2.67 per share. 
  • Wearable Devices (WLDS) shares were down 0.46% in pre-market trading.

data.title: Monumental Energy announces private placement offering of 10M-15M units
data.description:
• Monumental Energy (MNRG:CA) (MNMRF) intends to complete a non-brokered private placement of 10M-15M units at $0.05/unit for gross proceeds of a minimum of $500,000 and a maximum of up to $750,000.
  • Each unit will consist of one common share and one transferable common share purchase warrant.
  • Each warrant will entitle the holder to acquire one additional common share at a price of $0.08/share for a period of three years from the closing date of the Private Placement.
  • The company intends to use the net proceeds to fund the costs and expenses to formally enter into and fund additional workover projects with New Zealand Energy and L&M Energy, additional expenses at Copper Moki-1 and for general working capital purposes and corporate expenses.
